Title: Basis Invariants in Non--Abelian Gauge Theories
Author: Uwe M\"uller
Comments: 21 pages, 2 figures, 15 tables; LaTeX, uses epsfig; figure in Table 5
  and typo in Table 8 corrected
Report-no: DESY 96-154
\\
  A basis of Lorentz and gauge-invariant monomials in non--Abelian gauge
theories with matter is described, applicable for the inverse mass expansion of
effective actions. An algorithm to convert an arbitrarily given invariant
expression into a linear combination of the basis elements is presented. The
linear independence of the basis invariants is proven.
